HEADWORD: Staith
<hw>Staith</hw> <pr>(st⟦amac⟧th)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>stae⟦edh⟧</ets> a bank, shore, from the root of E.
<ets>stead</ets>.]</ety> <def>A landing place; an elevated staging upon
a wharf for discharging coal, etc., as from railway cars, into
vessels.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

